str2: That, that one there, yonder. From ekei; that one (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

parse: Verb - Present Imperative Middle or Passive - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To think, suppose, expect, imagine. Or oimai middle voice apparently from hoios; to make like, i.e. Imagine.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Middle - 3rd Person Singular
str2: (a) I receive, get, (b) I take, lay hold of.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Accusative Neuter Singular
str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.
Gen: from; dat: beside, in the presence of; acc: alongside of.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Lord, master, sir; the Lord. From kuros; supreme in authority, i.e. controller; by implication, Master.
